  ANALYSIS:
  TYPE = TWOLEVEL RANDOM;
  ESTIMATOR = BAYES;
  PROC = 8;
  FBITER = 50000;
  BSEED = 1213;

  MODEL:
  %WITHIN%
  resvar_1 | y1;
  resvar2-resvar20 | y2-y20;

  day_ar1 | y2 ON y1;
  day_ar2 | y3 ON y2;
  day_ar3 | y4 ON y3;
  day_ar4 | y5 ON y4;
  day_ar5 | y6 ON y5;
  day_ar6 | y7 ON y6;
  day_ar7 | y8 ON y7;

  day_ar14 | y15 ON y14;
  day_ar15 | y16 ON y15;
  day_ar16 | y17 ON y16;
  day_ar17 | y18 ON y17;
  day_ar18 | y19 ON y18;
  day_ar19 | y20 ON y19;

  night_ar | y1 ON y20&1;

  %BETWEEN%
  mu BY y1-y20@1;
  mu;
  [mu];
  [y1-y20@0];
  y1-y20@0;

  day_ar by day_ar1-day_ar19@1;
  day_ar*0.01;
  [day_ar*0.6];
  [day_ar1-day_ar19@0];
  day_ar1-day_ar19@0;

  night_ar*0.01;
  [night_ar*0.15];

  resvar BY resvar2-resvar20@1;
  resvar;
  [resvar];
  resvar2-resvar20@0;
  [resvar2-resvar20@0];

  mu night_ar day_ar resvar_1 resvar WITH
    mu night_ar day_ar resvar_1 resvar;

  OUTPUT:
  TECH1 TECH8 STDYX FSCOMPARISON STAND(CLUSTER);

  PLOT:
  TYPE = PLOT3;
  FACTOR = ALL (500);

  SAVEDATA:
  FILE IS pa_ar_step3.dat;
  SAVE IS FSCORES (500);
